The paper focuses on video object segmentation, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a modification to the one-shot video object segmentation (OSVOS) method. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new loss function and discusses its effectiveness, which falls under the scope of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves training a neural network, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions using different network structures as the backbone, which is related to multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for the proposed method to be generalized to other vision tasks, which could fall under the scope of robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well.
